      <pubtit>Mapping local heterogeneity in open twisted bilayer graphene devices</pubtit>
      <p><img src="/images/pubpic/TBG_SL.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>Why is there so much variation in TBG devices? And are open devices more disordered than encapsulated ones? We introduce a new method to continuously map inhomogeneities of a moirÃ© lattice and apply it to open-device TBG to show that twist angle variation is small over areas of hundreds of nm.</p>
      <p><em>T Benschop<em>, TA de Jong</em>, P Stepanov*, Xiaobo Lu, V Stalman, SJ van der Molen, DK Efetov, MP Allan</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2008.13766">arXiv:2008.13766</a></strong></p>
      <p class="text-danger"><strong> </strong></p>
      <p> </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <div class="well">
      <pubtit>Spatially dispersing Yu-Shiba-Rusinov states in the unconventional superconductor FeTe0.55Se0.45</pubtit>
      <p><img src="/images/pubpic/YSR.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>We report on a peculiar, spatially dispersing YSR state in Fe(Se,Te) that can be tuned by the tip.</p>
      <p><em>D Chatzopoulos, Doohee Cho, KM Bastiaans, GO Steffensen, D Bouwmeester, A Akbari, Genda Gu, J Paaske, BM Andersen, MP Allan</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2006.12840">arXiv:2006.12840</a></strong></p>
